{
  "analysis": "The comparison shows the terrain colors are inverted - where original has 67, my version has 152 and vice versa. The terrain colors (0.9 and 0.4) and lighting are correct, but the hash function selects the opposite color. I also see small ±1 differences in the sphere region from floating-point precision. I need to swap the terrain color selection and also check the exact terrain pattern.",
  "plan": "Fix the terrain color selection by swapping which color is chosen for odd/even hash. Then compile and compare. If terrain matches, focus on remaining sphere precision differences.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -i 's/((hx+hz)&1)?0.4f:0.9f/((hx+hz)&1)?0.9f:0.4f/' /app/mystery.c\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "gcc -static -o /tmp/reversed /app/mystery.c -lm 2>&1 | head -20\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "/tmp/reversed > /tmp/rev_out.txt 2>/tmp/rev_err.txt; cp /app/image.ppm /tmp/rev_img.ppm; /app/mystery > /tmp/orig_out.txt 2>/tmp/orig_err.txt; cp /app/image.ppm /tmp/orig_img.ppm; cmp /tmp/orig_img.ppm /tmp/rev_img.ppm && echo \"PPM MATCH\" || echo \"PPM DIFFER\"; cmp /tmp/orig_err.txt /tmp/rev_err.txt && echo \"STDERR MATCH\" || echo \"STDERR DIFFER\"\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "perl /tmp/cmp_ppm2.pl 2>&1 | head -20\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "perl /tmp/cmp_ppm2.pl 2>&1 | tail -5\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}
